 Ponting starts mind games 
Melbourne: Anil Kumble has been appointed Test captain just for the ensuing series against Pakistan, but even Ricky Ponting believes that the leg-spinner will lead India in the series against Australia. The Aussie captain has taken that for granted and started the mind games a month before the Indians land Down Under, saying that Kumble will find it very hard to cope with the pressures of captaincy. Kumble will be under pressure coming to Australia. Anyone who captains the Indian cricket team is always under a lot of pressure. A lot of very, very good players in the past havent been able to cope with that. (Sachin) Tendulkar probably didnt ever really want to do it, Ponting said after the 2-0 Test series win over Sri Lanka in Hobart on Tuesday. Even The Telegraph reported last week that everything pointed to Kumble being retained captain for the Australia series. (PTI) 
